description: A truly special car requires a special description. This is a 1979 Porsche 911SC hotrod. This 911 has lots of tasteful and aggrssive modifications on it. Before he had it a specialty shop in florida built the vehicle as a shop car/ weekend track car. The previous owner went over the car and made sure it was mechanically flawless and ready to drive. Engine and transmission have about 7 hours on them total.

The engine is a 3.0 liter single plug, there are ZERO oil leaks on this engine. Fresh fluids with dual carbs sitting on top. Engine is tuned to run perfect when its at operating temparature. The previous owner had the vehicle tuned and dynoed at 280 hp. The transmission is a freshly rebuilt 915 transmission and is in great condition, nice smooth throws in the gear box. There is no crunching or grinding of the synchronizers.
